Rating: 4
I made these as dessert for a birthday dinner and they were a huge hit. Very fussy and a little frustrating to make, but the lemon filling is to die for. Raspberries and lemon are one of my favorite combinations. My friend is very health conscious, so I lightened it a bit by using low-fat frozen yogurt. I have one left in the freezer, and I'm looking forward to enjoying it again tonight. If you're looking for an elegant dessert that is sure to wow your guests, this one is worth the trouble.

Rating: 4
I made these last night and they were a HIT!!! This recipe is definitely a keeper. I also used plastic wrap as another reviewer recommended. Also after each stage of freezing, I smoothed each layer with a warm spoon because I found the layers settled during freezing and it made a nicer presentation - especially with the first stage (the outer shell). I found I was able to cut down the total freezing times by about half - each layer froze much quicker than the recipe calls for. I also froze the lemon cream for about 1/2 hour before layering it in the dishes - which cut about 5 hours off the chilling time for that component.

